<subSubSection id="FED8F4394B06212C6D88526285E966E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="studied type specimens">
<paragraph id="21B3265E47A33D93952409B1D719CF07" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Studied type specimens.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00903C458CD263B30566BB0CF9022C2B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Panama • 1 ♂, holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="B81698D33C47BE49FBC6B45A3CC1C865" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microdon hermetia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hermetia">
<emphasis id="47A31FBD0DE7E419F082C37559630EAA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Microdon hermetia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Curran; Barro Colorado Island, Canal Zone; 23 Dec. 1928; C.H. Curran leg; AMNH. Label 1: &quot;Barro Colo Isld. / Canal Zone / XII-23-1928&quot;; label 2: &quot;Collector / C.H. Curran&quot;; label 3 (red): &quot;Microdon / hermetia / Curran. [male sign] / Holotype&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="416B043198E75C38BD7AFA15B921B8FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="EC1552C65591E8D5CEBA7864453D7F02" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0552A73ADCF81068DC93C12A8DA0E85E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body length: male 16 mm. The constricted abdomen, absence of a triangle of golden pile on the mesoscutum, and partly dark wings place this species in a group with 
<taxonomicName id="ABA739DB51093D2264A8F9DD6469490B" genus="P." lsidName="P. diaphanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="diaphanus">
<emphasis id="FA11FA9F727AD3A648682C114C2C3C7F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. diaphanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="25F4AE7526528848BB19F108F7D2E9DC" genus="P." lsidName="P. elongatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis id="031B8E746A3CD22E31E08E99F3839E53" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="7182B5A4F045C275CF9C0034D01E999C" genus="P." lsidName="P. hermetoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hermetoides">
<emphasis id="C9AC8B56DA75D4EBEF4BDC06E2A380D0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. hermetoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From 
<taxonomicName id="43CADE2D20275954EF1CF0B5572C2548" genus="P." lsidName="P. diaphanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="diaphanus">
<emphasis id="945469E8B23B803FBC2E0F2C8B867D3B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. diaphanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by tergite 2 being wider than long, from 
<taxonomicName id="FE4A4822604BF1EBDDF97BEA0DD89D51" genus="P." lsidName="P. elongatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis id="F73FEB7560AB776FFD36347647F6F8CA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of yellow in the vena spuria, from 
<taxonomicName id="CB3DFC19A0602026C661A387D2ECC338" genus="P." lsidName="P. hermetoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hermetoides">
<emphasis id="3BB1C4E909EEEDEB654F91FE95364806" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. hermetoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the partly hyaline wing cell bm. The male genitalia are figured in 
<figureCitation id="148A10E47C56E05EF6D621E184D14E91" captionStart="Figures 256–261" captionStartId="F44" captionText="Figures 256 - 261. Male genitalia of Peradon species 256 P. fenestratus French Guyana MNHN 257 P. aureoscutus holotype 258 P. aureus Ecuador CNC 259 P. trilinea holotype 260 P. trivittatus Suriname RMNH 261 P. hermetia holotype." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures256-261" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362314" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures256-261">Fig. 261</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
